# ─── Accepted CVEs ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This file suppresses false positive or accepted-risk vulnerability
# findings from Trivy scans.
#
# All CVEs listed here must be reviewed and documented before adding.

# CVE-2026-12151 — HIGH — undici (bundled with node:24-alpine)
#
# undici Denial of Service due to unbounded memory.
# Fixed in: 6.27.0, 7.28.0, 8.5.0
#
# This vulnerability is in the undici HTTP client bundled with the
# node:24-alpine base image itself. Our application dependencies
# all use undici@7.28.0 (patched). The Alpine image's bundled
# undici@6.26.0 is a Node.js runtime component that cannot be
# overridden via npm/pnpm. Accepted as a runtime risk; will be
# resolved when the node:24-alpine image is rebuilt with a newer
# Node.js patch version.
#
# Re-evaluate on next Node.js Docker image update.
CVE-2026-12151
